PREP: CLEAN: Wash hands. Prepare chicken according to package directions. Cut tenders in half crosswise. COOK: In a large skillet heat oil to medium-high; add vegetables and stir-fry 5 minutes. Add stir-fry sauce, orange juice and brown sugar. Continue cooking over medium heat 3 minutes. Toss cooked chicken with the vegetable mixture. SERVE: Serve over rice. Top with almonds. CHILL: Refrigerate leftovers immediately.